# Guards (mirrors .claude/hooks/*)

## Git Safety (git-guard.mjs)

NEVER execute these dangerous git operations:
- `git branch -D` / `git branch --delete --force` (force delete branch)
- `git push --force` / `git push --force-with-lease` (force push)
- `git commit` on main/master branch (protected branches)
- `git worktree remove --force` (discards uncommitted work)
- `git rebase -i` / `git add -i` (interactive — unsupported, blocks automation)
- NEVER amend a commit that has already been pushed, unless user explicitly asks for force push
- NEVER update the git config

If asked to do any of these, refuse and explain the risk.

## Linear Branch Commit Guard (linear-guard.mjs)

On Linear-tracked branches (`yuk-*`, `foundation-*`, `p<N>-*`, `feat/yuk-*`, `fix/yuk-*`),
ALL commits MUST include a `YUK-NN` reference.

- Each Linear issue must be referenced separately: `Closes YUK-27` + `Closes YUK-28`
- Do NOT write `Closes YUK-27 + YUK-28` (Linear only links the first one)
- Multiple issues require repeating the Linear keyword: `Fixes YUK-1` and `Fixes YUK-2`
- New planning/triage/roadmap work goes to Linear — do NOT use `gh issue create`

## JSON Edit Guard (json-edit-guard.mjs)

After editing any `.json` file, verify the result parses as valid JSON before proceeding
(e.g. `jq . <file> >/dev/null`). If invalid after the edit, fix it immediately.

## Post-Fetch Divergence (post-fetch-divergence.sh)

After running `git fetch` or `git pull`, report:
- Whether upstream has diverged from local
- The upstream commit author(s) of new commits

## Linear Closeout Reminder (linear-closeout-reminder.sh)

Before ending a session where you made code changes (commits or uncommitted edits),
remind the user to check Linear issue status sync per `docs/agents/issue-tracker.md`
"Closeout issue capture gate" section. Create/update Linear issues for actionable
follow-ups discovered; do not leave them only in chat/local TODOs.

## Post-Edit Lint (mirrors .claude/settings.json PostToolUse)

After writing/editing files:
- `.json` files: verify valid JSON
- `.ts` / `.tsx` / `.js` / `.jsx` / `.mjs` files: run `pnpm exec biome check <file>`
- Biome-only toolchain (no ESLint/Prettier): 2-space, 100 col, single quotes
